dymo-cups-drivers (1.4.0-12build3+loadfix5) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Act on findings from multi-tool static analysis (STATIC_ANALYSIS.md,
    covering cppcheck 2.19, clang-tidy 21.1.8, clang static analyzer,
    gcc -fanalyzer 15.2, flawfinder 2.0.19). Five fixes:
  * Fix 18 (S-2, S-3 HIGH): initialise CLabelManagerDriver::PageLineCount_
    and CNLLHalftoning::ImageWidth_/ImageHeight_ in their ctor init
    lists; reading them before a write was latent UB.
  * Fix 19 (S-5 HIGH): delete copy-ctor and copy-assignment on both
    CCupsPrintEnvironmentForDriver and ...ForLM. These classes own a
    raw FILE* and would double-fclose if accidentally copied.
  * Fix 20 (S-7 MEDIUM): replace atoi() with a range-checking strtol
    helper at the three PPD value parse sites in the LabelManager
    initializer. Overflow / malformed input now falls back to a
    caller-supplied default instead of silently producing 0.
  * Fix 21 (S-11 LOW): rewrite `for (size_t i = BufSize-1; i >= 0; --i)`
    as `for (size_t i = BufSize; i-- > 0; )` in LW and LM GetBlanks.
    The old loop terminated only by invariant (upstream caught by
    `else break;` at the first non-zero byte, plus a guard); the new
    idiom terminates by construction.
  * Fix 22 (S-1 HIGH): hoist the Process*Options LM parameter type
    from CDummyLanguageMonitor& to ILanguageMonitor&. Eliminates six
    sibling-class reinterpret_casts that were safe-by-accident
    (upstream callees don't dereference the parameter) but would
    become UB on any edit that did.
  * All fixes commented with cross-references to STATIC_ANALYSIS.md
    so a future reviewer can follow the trail. No runtime behaviour
    change on the happy path.

 -- loadfix <noreply@anthropic.com>  Mon, 27 Apr 2026 21:30:00 +1000

dymo-cups-drivers (1.4.0-12build3+loadfix4) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Delete src_v2/ entirely (~900KB, 0 files installed). The tree was
    DYMO's unfinished rewrite; independent review found it strictly
    worse than src/ on every axis relevant to the LW 450 family it
    targets (drops RLE compression, drops Twin Turbo subclasses, has
    an async-signal-unsafe signal handler, doesn't fix any of our
    earlier loadfix bugs, declares five member functions that are
    never implemented). The one feature worth salvaging would have
    been LW 550 / 5XL support, which is out of scope for this fork.
    Git history preserves the tree for anyone who wants to resurrect
    it.
  * Simplify Makefile.am and configure.ac back to their pre-Fix-7
    shape now that the dead tree isn't there to work around.

 -- loadfix <noreply@anthropic.com>  Mon, 27 Apr 2026 20:45:00 +1000

dymo-cups-drivers (1.4.0-12build3+loadfix3) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Act on findings from independent code-review (BUGS.md). Seven
    additional fixes targeting LabelManager parity and hardening:
  * BUG-1.1 (Critical): null-check DEVICE_URI in LM IsLocal() to
    avoid SIGSEGV on strncmp(NULL, ...).
  * BUG-1.2 (Critical): initialise CLabelManagerLanguageMonitor::
    TapeWidth_ in the ctor — was read uninitialised on page 1.
  * BUG-2.1 (Major): guard unsigned underflow in
    NonLinearLaplacianHalftoning::ProcessImage block-loop condition.
  * BUG-2.2 + BUG-2.5 (Major): bounds-check Status[0] / Status[1]
    in LM CheckStatus / CheckTapeSize; break inner poll loop on a
    read-failure instead of spinning; mirrors Fix 2 on the LM side.
  * BUG-3.7 + BUG-3.8 (Moderate): add missing <unistd.h> / <fcntl.h>
    includes (compiles today via transitive luck; may break on
    musl / older toolchains).
  * BUG-3.9 (Moderate): zero-init struct sigaction so
    implementation-private fields don't hold stack garbage.
  * BUG-3.11 (Moderate): mirror Fix 1 on the LM filter —
    IsBackchannelSupported() now returns false for raster2dymolm
    too, avoiding the same zombie-job failure class on LabelManager
    hardware.
  * BUG-4.2 (Minor): delete "DYMO LabelLabelWriter DUO Tape" typo
    block (dead code, byte-identical to a sibling block above).
  * BUG-4.7 (Minor): delete duplicate AUTO_CUTTER_BIT / NO_POWER_BIT
    enumerators (both unused, both = 0x80, contradictory semantics).

 -- loadfix <noreply@anthropic.com>  Mon, 27 Apr 2026 20:15:00 +1000

dymo-cups-drivers (1.4.0-12build3+loadfix2) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Act on findings from independent spec-conformance review against
    "DYMO LabelWriter 450 Series Technical Reference" Rev. 10/09
    (committed as TECH_REVIEW.md).
  * F-1 (MEDIUM): rename PAPER_FEED_BIT -> PAPER_JAM_BIT and route
    ESC-A status bit 6 to jsSlotStatusError instead of jsPaperOut.
    A real paper jam now surfaces in CUPS as
    com.dymo.slot-status-error, not com.dymo.out-of-paper-error.
  * F-3, F-4, F-7 (LOW): comment the non-spec ESC Q emission in
    StartDoc (LW 3xx workaround); document that the 156-ESC reset is
    a sync-recovery not a firmware-default reset; correct the dormant
    PageHeight_ default from 0x0800 (2048) to the spec's documented
    3058.
  * F-5, F-8, F-11 (LOW/INFO): document that ESC B per raster line,
    idempotent StartDoc parameter re-sends, and the 4XL MaxPrintWidth
    override are deliberate trade-offs / outside-spec-scope, with
    inline comments explaining what to do if anyone wants to change
    them.
  * No behavioural change for the LW 450 family end-to-end print path
    vs. loadfix1. The F-1 fix activates only if someone re-enables
    the back-channel language monitor in a future patch.

 -- loadfix <noreply@anthropic.com>  Mon, 27 Apr 2026 19:30:00 +1000

dymo-cups-drivers (1.4.0-12build3+loadfix1) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Non-maintainer upload fixing the "zombie print job" issue on DYMO
    LabelWriter 450 / 450 Turbo / 450 DUO Label / 450 Twin Turbo over USB.
  * Disable the back-channel status monitor in raster2dymolw (the loop was
    broken: first byte of multi-byte reply used, no read-failure exit,
    unbounded PollUntilPaperIn) — see CHANGES.md in the source tree.
  * Initialise CCupsPrintEnvironmentForLM members (undefined-behaviour
    read of JobStatus_ could early-abort print jobs).
  * Install SIGTERM/SIGINT/SIGPIPE handlers so CUPS cancels and backend
    pipe failures result in clean filter termination (ESC E flushed,
    stdout closed) rather than leaving the CUPS scheduler in "now
    printing" state forever.
  * Explicitly close stdout before return so the USB backend sees EOF
    immediately on job completion.
  * Return 0 on empty CUPS-raster input instead of marking the job
    aborted in the queue.
  * Exclude src_v2/ from the build (uses std::auto_ptr, removed in C++17).
  * Drop redundant Debian patches already applied in the matthiasbock
    upstream fork (0003, 0006, 0007, 0008, 0010).

 -- loadfix <noreply@anthropic.com>  Mon, 27 Apr 2026 18:00:00 +1000

